{
 "name": "RPlog_Tyy_sun_Hunt",
 "title": "Tyy'sun's Hunt: Cornered on Ord Mantell",
 "summary": "On the New Republic crossroads world of Ord Mantell, the operative Ash (Nitisha, alias Ja'casha) is shadowed across the starport by the surveillance network of the Twi'lek maffi of New Kala'uun, who corner her aboard a train and at a cafe at the behest of their crimelord, Tyy'sun Eson. Eson demands she repay a 'debt' owed for her past ties to Tritus, whose organization aided the Hutt Draga in the slaughter of Twi'leks, but Ash defiantly refuses, hurling hot coffee at his agent A'estshy (Shy) and calling for aid. A volatile standoff erupts as Eson confronts a parade of figures from his past--the Mandalorian Cantrell, the Sith fringer Axel Vichten, the Quarren warrior Thrask, and a disguised Bothan spy Besk--with weapons, a thermal detonator, and rifles drawn amid Eson's mounting rage. Recognizing the moment is wrong for battle and that his diminished power can no longer dominate his enemies, Eson stands down, ordering Axel off his streets and demanding he deliver the agents of the Twi'lek inquisition, before withdrawing with his Family, A'estshy, and Thrask as his strange allies.",
